-- England Cricket Names Graham Gooch as Full-Time Batting Coach
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-02-18T16:13:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-18/england-cricket-names-graham-gooch-as-full-time-batting-coach.html
Graham Gooch was named the  England 
cricket team’s batting coach on a full-time basis.  Gooch has been working as a conultant batting coach since
November 2009 and will start his full-time post March 5 as
England prepares for its Test series against  Sri Lanka , the
England and Wales Cricket Board said in a statement.  “Graham is an outstanding coach and is held in the highest
regard by all those who work alongside him,” England Managing
Director Hugh Morris said. “His record as a player and a coach
is formidable and he has shown over the past couple of years
that he has a huge amount to offer.”  Gooch played 118 Test matches and 125 one-day matches for
England, scoring 13,120 total runs.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  